					<head>Compendium</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n80017842" rend="visible">
						<summary>A halakhic commentary.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n80017842">
							<locus from="1r" to="158v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush hilkhot ha-Ri"f (῾Eruvin)</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש הלכות הרי"ף (ערובין)</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/90404354">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/53421753" xml:lang="en">Hananel ben Samuel, active 13th century</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/53421753" xml:lang="he">חננאל בן שמואל</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>A commentary on Alfasi's compendium of ῾Eruvin by Hananel ben Samuel.</p>
								<p>Various readings are often mentioned, e.g., 54v, 67r.</p>
								<p>Occasionally Arabic is used, e.g., folio 18v, 68r.</p>
								<p>Folios 1-3 and some of the marginal notes (e.g., folios 7v, 14r, 26r) were probably written by the author himself.</p>
								<p>The diagrams, with lettering, are apparently also autograph.</p>
							</note>
							<decoNote type="diagram">
								<locus n="23r, 26v, 36r"/>Diagrams.</decoNote>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 13th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<extent>158 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>245</height>
										<width>165</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>195</height>
										<width>110</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>158 folios (+ 3 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 4 at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 10 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Damaged at the beginning.</p>
									<p>Much worm-eaten, without loss of text.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="25" writtenLines="25">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso. </p>
									<p>Some pages left blank for diagrams.</p>
									<p>Corrections (e.g., folio 8r, 16v).</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Oriental square script of the 13th century. Partly an autograph of Hananel ben Samuel.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">
								<p>
									<locus from="1r" to="3v"/> in a different but contemporary hand.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
